entries.femaleVariant: What the--? You out of your fucking mind?
Looking for Evelyn Parker. Know where she might be?
I'm looking for Evelyn Parker.
Where'll I find Woodman?
Who's Tom?
Where'll I find Woodman?
Who's this Tom?
Nuh-uh, I'm done. I could get fired for all the shit I've told you already. Just... get out.
Parker? Oooh, that was some drama… Don't know who started it, though – client or her…
He and Evelyn – besties. If you wanna know more, he's your guy.
Back office, upstairs... Are you sure you wanna do that, though?
Hi, I'm Skye. And you must be... Valerie?
entries.maleVariant: Hi, I'm Skye. And you must be... Vincent?

entries.femaleVariant: So, V, you're dying.
OK, then. V.
V. Just V. Only people who know me real well can use my real name.
It's just "V."
Afterlife.
You gotta help me. Please…
I'm no threat. But she could be in trouble. Just wanna talk to her, find out if she's OK.
In case you haven't noticed, doll work's not the most secure job in the world. One day you're in, the next you're out, and maybe gone.
Anything out of the ordinary happen here lately?
What's going on?
Goddamn thing threw me out!
Talk? You pulled the emergency brake, ripped me out just to talk?
I need this info. Name your price.
Fuck you, your eddies and that girl of yours. I could get fired for doing something like this.
I'll make it worth your while.
All right, fine, hand it over and get out before you land me in the shit.
First, tell me what you know about Evelyn.
[Stand] I'll pay for info.
[Stand] Need your help. Please.
[Stand] You're good looking. It'd be a shame to lose that.
Answer the question. Do it. And then you can get back to whatever it is you do.
Here's what I don't do. Spill to any rando who walks in here.
How about those good looks of yours? Be a shame if they dipped below club standards…
Wonder what happens to a doll that suddenly goes ugly…
entries.maleVariant: I wonder what happens to a doll that suddenly goes ugly…

entries.femaleVariant: Now, Evelyn Parker – I know you know something. So talk.
Fine. Heard a customer did a number on her. But that's all I know.
Shit like that happens around here way more often than anybody'd care to admit.
You oughta ask Tom. Two of them were inseparable, gossiping for hours on end.
Who's Tom?
A customer attacked her?
Where did it happen?
Who's Tom?
A doll like the rest of us. What'd you think – an XBD star?
Where'll I find him?
VIP area. Booth two. I think.
Thanks. See? You turned out to be useful after all.
A customer attacked her?
I guess... I dunno, real mess that was. Security barged in, handled it. Things went silent.
You don't go around asking questions here. Better off not seeing, not hearing, keeping your head down.
Evelyn Parker. What do you know about her?
Not much. Everyone's got their own booths, their own problems, their own little bubbles.
It's a fragile ecosystem. People like you barge in, violate it, try to rearrange. No.
[Sit] What do you know about Evelyn?
This wasn't what I expected.
Thanks for the chat. That was refreshing.
Gotta say, that wasn't what I expected. I was hoping for thrills, not some gloomy, soul-searching debate.
Look, baby, I don't decide what happens in here. Your subconscious drives everything.
Mh. Next time, remind me to tell my subconscious to go fuck itself.
entries.maleVariant: Hm. Next time, remind me to tell my subconscious to go fuck itself.

entries.femaleVariant: Um... just don't tell anyone about this, OK?
I came here to talk to you, Skye, not some soppy algorithm.
Lotta things been going on in my head lately. But this was... different. Refreshing.
That's what we do at Clouds.
I get why people come here, come back... but... I need something else.
entries.maleVariant: I get why people come here, come back... but I need something else.

entries.femaleVariant: Lookin' for someone named Evelyn Parker. Used to work here. Know her? Know where she is?
You need answers, that's clear... Just not the ones you think you need.
Asked you a simple question.
Evelyn Parker… not the most important thing you're looking for, is she? I can smell your fear. You're afraid of something else.
Think you know me well? OK, tell me what I'm so afraid of.
It's something you don't talk about.
Everybody's entitled to secrets. Got my own with good reason, too.
Say it. Say it out loud. Not for me, but for yourself.
I was told this place'd fulfill my deepest desires. Not what I was expecting, this.
When true desires go unfulfilled, they turn into needs. We are here to reach for them and beyond, we are here to understand.
So what is it I need so badly?
To come to terms with the fact that you died. Now move on, already.
That's tough. Rather let it eat away at me a bit more.
Come to terms… Sure, lemme just curl up here on the floor and wait for... whatever.
Give up. That's what you're saying.
You're scared because you've given up on your dreams.
What happened to becoming the best in all of Night City?
Wasn't so long ago I really wanted that.
But then all this shit happened. Seems like I was living in dreamland.
entries.maleVariant: But then all this shit happened. Seems like I was living in a dreamland.

entries.femaleVariant: Still wanna be the best... Never gave up on that goal.
Chances of getting there're starting to look pretty slim, though.
Just answer my question. Tell me where Evelyn is. Don't have time for a… debate.
Why'd the manager say she doesn't work here anymore? When was Evelyn last here? You know anything?
Evelyn had her own story before it collided with yours.
Just want the world to know I was here. That I mattered.
entries.maleVariant: I just want the world to know I was here. That I mattered.

entries.femaleVariant: Instead of a dream, you're living a nightmare. You're afraid of being erased, as if you never existed.
The people I've lost live on in my thoughts. And that's what I'll be – a memory.
Or just an annoying little voice in someone else's head.
Think I might just be... afraid. So I imagine these things to distract myself from the thought of... the void.
'Cause that's about what greeted me before…
Fear is your most effective weapon in the fight against death.
I snuffed it once and I'm gonna do it all over again. Got no idea how to stop it. There, happy?
Had a true friend, once. Now he's gone.
Everything you need you already carry inside you.
Not about to have this conversation with you.
Ah, a hard shell for everyone to see. You think even thinking about it undermines you, makes you soft.
Don't survive in Night City by bein' weak.
entries.maleVariant: Don't survive in Night City by being weak.

entries.femaleVariant: Death is death is death. You're gone – game over.
You can't know that for certain. Even if you've been there and back.
Believe me, I've seen it. And it's fucking boring.
You haven't stopped grieving since, or for what's to come.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
Samurai.
How'd you know I'm dying?
Deep inside... you fear this, cower before it.
Of all the voices in your head, the loudest is that calling for help. Look around, all of this is your doing.
There's something in those mirrors, way back...
It's a projection – your inner landscape.
Just what I needed – therapy with a robohooker.
I'm not here to analyze you. That's not something I do.
Where'd it happen?
Her booth. Told you, she was with a client.
Gonna just stand there or tell me a number?
Eleven.
I'm afraid of becoming someone else, forgetting who I am.
You're already becoming someone else, every second of every day.
Still, I feel... a connection between who I was and who I'm turning into.
What you really fear is becoming someone you don't recognize in the least.
You don't see death as destruction, the end, but as a change.
I'm not grieving.
Grief doesn't begin to describe it.
What I've been through – tough to move on from that.
Wasn't enough I died once. Have to go and do it again.
Death's' absurdity, the futile struggle before – these terrify you.
What's past is past. I'm over it.
You're in denial – don't you see?
Would it change things even by a hair if I wasn't?
Need to get inside that booth somehow.
Yeah? And do what?
None of your biz. Can you open it or not?
Sure, just don't bother me again. Ever. Talk to Tom.
I'm looking for a girl.
How do you know I'm dying?
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
I'm looking for someone.
There's something in those mirrors.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
How do I get in?
Is it occupied now?
This booth occupied now?
Nah, I think it's been "out of order" since, uh…
Fear isn't a weakness. It's there to protect you.
Or is it just the fear of becoming someone else, different?
But I know you'll find her. You always get your way.
You just gonna talk in circles, that it?
I can't help you if you don't want to be helped.
From what? Losing myself? Becoming a stranger in my own body?
entries.maleVariant: From what? Losin' myself? Becomin' a stranger in my own body?

entries.femaleVariant: What's next? Meditation?
Something like that. Try me.
That thought alone could save your life.
Need to talk to you.
Look, I don't know anyone named Evelyn.
What'm I afraid of?
This is what "fulfilling my deepest desires" looks like?
Tell me where Evelyn is.
Just gonna talk in circles, in riddles?
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
I died and now I'm dying again. Happy?
We're not having this conversation.
I'm alone, got nobody left.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
You can't come to terms with something like that.
So I just give up?
Still wanna be the best.
Pure fantasy, that.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Lie down] Not gonna die completely.
[Lie down] The void freaks me out.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
I'm scared of the unknown, of dying again.
Can't imagine what it's like to become someone else.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
There anything you DO know?
You're talkin' to the wrong doll, honey. You really wanna know, talk to Tom. Even better – Woodman.
He work here?
Pick o' the litter at Clouds. He's over in the VIP area. Booth two.
Just said I should, didn't you?
They'll kill you if you try.
And why's that? What's this Woodman do?
It's OK. Calm down.
Calm down. Just wanna ask you a question.
I'll calm down when you leave me alone. Get out! Now!
How fast I leave depends on how fast you answer.
So what now?
Now you find out what it is you need to do.
Which is? You're gonna tell me?
You've never backed down from anything in your life, even when you maybe should've.
You go through Night City knowing a stray bullet could end you while hailing a cab.
But that's never stopped you from taking action, going where you needed to go. And it won't stop you now.
But how do I keep up with everything that's changing...?
You have been keeping up. You've made an impact. Not a single thing in this world isn't in the process of becoming something else. Likewise you.
Never look back. If you gotta kill, kill. If you gotta burn it all to the ground, then let it burn.
So what now?
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
Thanks, um... for all this.
Jeez. Don't even feel like getting up…
Few do. But everything has its end.
What happened? I do something wrong?
Death was something that happened to other people – hell, that I DEALT to others. Now my number'll be up.
Thank you.
So what if I do? Why do you care?
I'm here to fulfill your deepest, most hidden desire.
Soon I'll be gone too. 'Cept, won't have anyone by my side.
Fear of death is what drives us all to do what we do.
[Sit] This'll be interesting...
Welp, looks like this'll be interesting…
[Touch] Not sure I can manage…
Start talking.
Notice anything unusual?
You're good looking. It'd be a shame to lose that.
Anyone 'sides me come around lookin' for her?
Hey... Talk to me?
If you're done here, you should go.
An enny for your thoughts.
Silent… why?
This some kind of seizure?
Ghost now, or I'll call security.
[Open]
What do you know about Evelyn?
If it's money you want, name your price.
Please, help me.
Wouldn't want to lose your good looks now, would you?
